		<name>Lufthansa Mail Service to South America in 1934-1939</name>
		<description>
			The Schwabenland (before Schwarzenfels) was a carrier for the german Lufthansa,
      placed near Bathurst (now Banjul, Gambia).
      The second carrier was placed near South America on Fernando de Noronha, called Westfalen
      With catapults it was possible to fire up seaplanes like the DO-J f Bos (Wal).
      Before the second world war, Lufthansa managed a mail traffic with this two carrier between
      Germany and South America.
